    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>One of the most convenient and amazing aspects of the wireless Web was not even mentioned in ''Meet the New Web. Same as the Old Web'' (Sept. 28), about wireless Web access for cell phones, pagers and personal digital assistants: the ability to read one's e-mail literally anywhere.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>One of the most convenient and amazing aspects of the wireless Web was not even mentioned in ''Meet the New Web. Same as the Old Web'' (Sept. 28), about wireless Web access for cell phones, pagers and personal digital assistants: the ability to read one's e-mail literally anywhere.</p>
        <p>Through my Sprint PCS phone, I can get access to my AOL account within seconds and get e-mail even when the account is ''signed on'' by another member of my family. The wireless Web has quickly become an indispensable tool in both my business and personal life.</p>
        <p>MORTON LANDOWNE  New York</p>
      </block>
